HEADWORD: Proponent
<hw>Pro*po"nent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who makes a proposal, or lays down a
proposition.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The propounder of a
thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proportion</ent>⟦br⟧
